The paper proposes a new off-policy learning algorithm for reinforcement learning that addresses the issue of biased estimates in noisy environments. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given the focus on learning algorithms and their performance in noisy environments, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories. However, the emphasis on control and optimization suggests that cs.RO and cs.SY are also relevant. Finally, the use of neural networks and stochastic processes suggests that cs.NE is a possible category as well.
